{"blocks":[{"key":"3jt24","text":"   Prepare a 1 mg/mL solution of the dye.

  LI-COR supplies vials of reactive dye in lyophilized form. You must resuspend the dye in an organic solvent (anhydrous DMSO) before use.


 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"df4a8","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":1,"key":0}],"data":[]}],"entityMap":[{"type":"notes","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":"<p><em>WARNING: DO NOT resuspend the contents of the dye vial in aqueous solution or buffer. The NHS ester reactive group is quickly hydrolyzed and inactivated by water. If you resuspend in aqueous buffer, you must use the entire dye vial immediately and discard all remaining dye after first use, because it will quickly hydrolyze during storage and become nonreactive.</em></p>"}]}
